{
  "text": "We use the Stanford Online Products dataset consisting of 120, 053 images with 22, 634 classes crawled from Ebay. The classes are grouped into 12 superclasses (e.g. cup, bicycle) which are used for mini-batch preparation following the procedure proposed in [CITATION_1] . We follow the evaluation protocol proposed in [CITATION_2] , using 59, 551 images corresponding to 11, 318 classes for training and 60, 502 images corresponding to 11, 316 classes for testing.",
